The series is geometric with first term \(a=12\) and common ratio \(r=\tfrac12\).  Hence the sum of the first \(n\) terms is

\[
S_n \;=\; a\,\frac{1-r^n}{1-r}
\;=\;
12\;\frac{1-(\tfrac12)^n}{1-\tfrac12}
\;=\;
12\;\frac{1-2^{-n}}{\tfrac12}
\;=\;
24\bigl(1-2^{-n}\bigr).
\]

For \(n=9\) this gives

\[
S_9 = 24\Bigl(1-2^{-9}\Bigr)
=24\Bigl(1-\tfrac1{512}\Bigr)
=24\cdot\tfrac{511}{512}
=\frac{12264}{512}
=\frac{1533}{64}
\approx23.953125.
\]

The set \{1,3,5,…,99\} has (99–1)/2+1 = 50 elements.  Hence its power set has  
   2^{50}  
subsets (including the empty set).
